The financial forecast shall include the following components:
A schedule of operating expenses;
A schedule of revenues, including concessions income, investment income, other income, and transfers from the Department;
A schedule of toll revenues, including the average toll per vehicle, the average toll increase, the number of paid vehicles, and the toll revenue by toll facility by fiscal year;
A schedule of planned bond issuances, including a detailed summary of bonds issued to fund the capital program and bonds issued to fund capitalized interest;
A schedule of debt service in each fiscal year for each bond issuance of all debt issued by the Authority, including debt service estimates of planned bond issuances; and
A summary schedule for the Authority that includes:
The total cash balance;
The amount of the cash balance that is encumbered;
The annual cash surplus or deficit;
Revenues;
Transfers to the Department from the Authority;
Transfers to the Authority from the Department;
Bond sales;
Expenditures for debt service;
Operating expenses;
Capital expenses;
Maintenance and operations expense reserve accounts;
Forecasted bond interest rates;
Total bonds outstanding; and
Financial coverage ratios, including the ratio of total cash to toll revenues, the debt service coverage ratio, and the rate covenant compliance ratio.
